      <h5 class="mb-2">Item Card</h5>
      <p>There was information we wanted to communicate as quickly as possible:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Tag</strong> (Is it new? Restocked? On Special?) Driving excitement was key to the success of this feature</li>
        <li><strong>Photo</strong> a sizable &amp; high-quality photo is necessary to catch the eye</li>
        <li><strong>Customized?</strong> a substantive amount of our orders are customized with the organizations logo</li>
        <li><strong>Cost</strong> Can the user afford it right now? Or will they have to save up?</li>
        <li><strong>Brand</strong> A key strategic advantage is our high-quality purchasing. We use this to differentiate ourselves from other recognition programs</li>
        <li><strong>Key Actions</strong> Has it been added to your wishlist or shopping cart? Previously, these actions were much deeper into the flow. It didn't cultivate the type of entertaining experience we want to cultivate</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

